 light on the often convoluted politics of war crimes justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aLawyerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMalmedy Massacre, 1944-1945. 0aWar crime trialszGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocities. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081479366440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814795125423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814795125/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK